#prodigy-task-05

Weather App with OpenWeatherMap API
This is a simple weather application that allows users to search for the weather conditions in a specific city. It utilizes the OpenWeatherMap API to retrieve weather data.

Features:

User can enter a city name in the search bar.

Upon submission, the app fetches weather data from the OpenWeatherMap API using the city name and API key (replace 5597863733bd67b645dec32cbedb464d with your own).

Displays the current temperature, weather description, and weather icon.

Displays additional details like feels like, humidity, and wind speed.

Technologies Used:

HTML: Provides the structure of the web page.
CSS: Styles the layout and appearance of the app.
JavaScript: Handles user interaction, fetches data from the API, and updates the UI.
